node.text: WOW. I haven’t been that nervous in a VERY long time! Put me on tv, fine, totally chill about it, but make the throw a baseball in front of an entire stadium of people...?! I DIDN’T PLAY SPORTS WITH BALLS, Y’ALL 😂 extremely uncomfortable to say the least 😆 very glad I got to share this awesome moment with my dad who was always a talented baseball player even though my practice throws were so much better 🙄😂 at least it was a straight shot and that my Dad scooped it in for the win 👏🏼 Thanks for making me look good, Dad. Love you! ❤️ And thanks to all of y’all cheering me on in the crowd! Afterwards my Dad said, “you got more of a cheer from the crowd than Dirk did!” 😆 When having a community of strong, loud women works in your favor 🤜🏼🤛🏼😍 Love y’all biiiiiiig time! And thanks to the Texas Rangers for this amazing opportunity that I’ll never forget!

node.title: Throwing the first pitch of a Texas Rangers baseball game to my Dad ❤️🥳

node.text: 😂 the twisty floppy falling challenge. It looked so easy and I came in WAY too confident. I take full responsibility for jacking this one up as a would not flip. I have three kids... I can’t die yet. 😆 We got the first part down though, right? RIGHT?! 😂🔥 What’s the next challenge. We’re REAL good at failing. What’s the name of this challenge?

node.title: Another challenge I don’t know the name of.

node.text: FINALLY Y’ALL! 😂👏🏼😭 So many feelings about MARCH 25th 7pm CST/ 8 pm EST. A lot of y’all have been with me through this entire wild ride which honestly is the most emotional part about this for me. Y’all ARE PART OF THIS. I was talking to y’all in between takes, showing behind the scene info, pushing the boundaries a little bit (thank you @hgtv 👏🏼😬) I know how insanely cheesy this sounds, I really do, but y’all were with me. On days I though, man, this isn’t as glamorous as I thought it would be 😰😂 I’d jump on stories and y’all were ALWAYS cheering me on 😭 *literally tearing up* I know every person on the internet thinks they have the best community, but no. Y’all are it. ❤️This group has impacted my life in ways I never knew was possible and I am forever grateful for you! 😭❤️ FOREVER grateful. THANK YOU. God is good all the time. Now, let’s renovate 20 homes, shall we? 😉 #nodemoreno *okay, but maybe some light demo* 😂 Will be available on both HGTV and Discovery+

node.text: My most recent DIY project in one of my homes we’re renovating...IT’S DONE 🙌🏼 I wanted a subtle change and the yellow gone 👋🏼 Please keep in mind that we still have to paint the cabinets, door, trim, green walls not green, etc 😬 all of it. All of it still needs a facelift BUT the fireplace is DONE! I knew I didn’t want to paint the stone white so I experimented in a homemade “gray wash” using paint I had from my garage and water 🥳 I used Sherwin Williams Versatile Gray because it’s had a more brown base that I knew wouldn’t turn blue on me in certain lighting and mixed it with a little more than double it’s amount with water. So like, 30% paint/ 70% water. Of course I didn’t measure 😂 it’s SUPER watery which makes it messy but it’s so fun and easy! Took me about 45 minutes total for the gray-washing 👍🏼 I took my time on the dry brushing part simply because it was therapeutic 🤗 Took me about 45 minutes as well! If you have yellow stone- YOU CAN DO THIS! Start with A LOT of water, you can always add paint into your mixing bowl but you can’t take back too much paint once it’s on your stone 😉 Who would try this?! Do you like it better than the yellow?! I can’t go back to the yellow brick sooooo... HOPE YOU LOVE IT! 😂❤️

node.title: Making yellow stone GRAY DIY tutorial 😍

node.text: WE BOUGHT A BREWERY. Mike’s pumped, I’m just along for the ride 😂 @armorcoffee will be expanding into the brew business 🥳 While Armor will continue to expand as a coffee brand (God willing🙏🏼❤️) Mike really felt that it had another part that was missing - craft beer! This already established brewery will be renovated and rebranded before we announce it’s exact location in Allen, Texas along with Armor Coffee Co. We plan to also serve coffee at this location as well as have a tap room for craft beer lovers to sit and enjoy 🤗 Days like these are a crazy bag of emotions… while we want to tell ALL of you news we’ve been keeping for a few months now, it’s also super scary 😬😆 If God wants @armorcoffee to grow, then it will grow. Location #2… let’s do this! ☕️🍻 God is good, all the time. *This is also my public promise that we will be making a low calorie beer that us women will love- there, I said it 😉❤️*

node.text: How many little sisters do we have in this group?! Tell me you’re a little sister without tell me you’re a little sister - it’s the dangling feet for me 😂 The little ones always get picked up and moved without consent 😆 Vivienne got over her fear of the trampoline today totally on her own. She’s been super resistant to it, I think because it was cage-like 😂 it takes the perfect gentle sister Berk to ease her into stuff! All three kids will use it - NOW it’s worth the money 👏🏼😆 who’s the youngest in the fam?! 🙋🏼‍♀️ That’s not me raising my hand #oldest #proudtattletaler #ifisawititoldit #brotherslovedit #lovingsister #butalsowatchyourback 😂

node.text: Michael Todryk, you are my kind of weird. Not only do I feel like God has blessed me with a best friend in marriage you are also the most amazing Dad to our children, which means more to me than anything ❤️ Mike you are naturally the best kind of Dad. Being a good dad comes easy for you, something that I know is God given and a huge blessing to our family. Thanks for being so amazing to us ❤️ And thanks for doing all the weird things with me and being cool with me posting it to the internet so a few of my closest friends can watch it. 😉😂 I honestly can’t imagine blindfolding and shoving pickled canned salmon into anyone else’s mouth while live on the internet… I really just can’t. 🥰❤️ Happy Father’s Day, babe. *this is as sappy as I get and I’ll only do it for you.* Happy Father’s Day to ALL the Dads! God bless you all! ❤️

node.text: What’s one thing you learned from your Dad? This is probably the coolest picture I have with my Dad ❤️ Happy early Father’s Day to the dad who makes all the rest seem “average” 🥰 Celebrated with him and the family tonight, super grateful for what I’ve been given in my life, especially strong relationships like this one. The thing that sticks out in my mind as far as what my Dad taught me is to not worry about things I can’t control. “Can you control this situation at all?”… “no…” “okay, so why are your stressing about it? You can’t change it, quit giving it your mental energy.” Advice that I still have to remind myself of pretty often 🙈 He also told me, “don’t take no sh*t, Jenn.” but that’s a story for another post. 😂 Gotta love dads. Love you, Dad. ❤️

node.text: Take us back to Colorado please 🥵😂 our room alone is 88 degrees right now… no AC in the Summer time is just a real joy! 🤗 What is the temperature where you are?! Is it hotter than normal everywhere?! Did y’all hear Viv’s little voice in stories today? I’m a sucker for her. A SUCKER. If I could have another Viv I’d be pregnant tomorrow. 😆 for real though. #mikesexcitedreadingthis #actuallyprobablynot #yeahnohesnot

node.text: Do you like baths? My bath has been ready for me since 2pm when I took this picture 😂 Peppa pig and family awaits! *zoom in* Y’all, this bathroom was WAY out of my comfort zone design wise. I can confidently say that I have never had marble-looking walls 😂 but holy MOLY, I love the way it turned out 😍 It’s official name is “Statuario” which I got from @daltile when I was renovating the new house. I knew I wanted something different, something I had never done in design before and I figured that our bathroom was the safest place to do it in because, well, if I hated it Mike and I would be the only one to witness it 😆 so glad it worked out for me so Mike didn’t have ammo 😎 and it’s so easy to clean! Like wiping down a countertop 👏🏼 Would you ever consider a bold wall like this in your home? I feel like we will be seeing more of this in many different home designs in the years to come 😉 #daltilepartner

node.text: We’re all about that fake grass, y’all 😂👏🏼 Did you see stories?! TURF. And SPEEDWALK RACES. I about peed my pants watching Mike 😆 It’s crazy because this grass matches all the greenery and the scenery that we live in like it was suppose to be here all along- when in reality nothing can grow because of all the trees! That was our reason... the past two houses we’ve lived in we haven’t had grass, we had snake filled ivy pits and mud 😂 now with a dog, *fake* grass a must. Gary made us do it. Excited to see it done! Do you have turf? Would you try turf?!

node.text: WOW. I haven’t been that nervous in a VERY long time! Put me on tv, fine, totally chill about it, but make the throw a baseball in front of an entire stadium of people...?! I DIDN’T PLAY SPORTS WITH BALLS, Y’ALL 😂 extremely uncomfortable to say the least 😆 very glad I got to share this awesome moment with my dad who was always a talented baseball player even though my practice throws were so much better 🙄😂 at least it was a straight shot and that my Dad scooped it in for the win 👏🏼 Thanks for making me look good, Dad. Love you! ❤️ And thanks to all of y’all cheering me on in the crowd! Afterwards my Dad said, “you got more of a cheer from the crowd than Dirk did!” 😆 When having a community of strong, loud women works in your favor 🤜🏼🤛🏼😍 Love y’all biiiiiiig time! And thanks to the Texas Rangers for this amazing opportunity that I’ll never forget!
